Shot in Great Smoky Mountains National Park, Gatlinburg, and Knoxville, Tennessee

Based on the novel by Rachel Maddux, A Walk in the Spring Rain is a romantic drama directed by Guy Green and adapted to screenplay by Sterling Siliphant. Taking a break from New York, Libby Meredith moves to a small house in backwoods Tennessee with her husband, Roger, who is on sabbatical to write a book. Their neighbor, Will Cade, is very helpful to them and to Libby especially. With her intellectual husband paying her little attention, she comes to like the country life and finds herself attracted to Will's rural sensibilities.


